<tip category="Digikam|General">
<html>
<p>Did you know that Digikam supports <b>Drag'n'Drop</b>? So you could easily move images from Konqueror to Digikam or from Digikam to K3b by simply "Drag'n'Drop" them.
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|General">
<html>
<p>Did you know that you could use the album collection feature go get your Photos sorted into two level? 1st, the collection than the album!
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|General">
<html>
<p>Did you know that the Properties entry of each photo gives you access to the properties entry of the Konqueror?
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|General">
<html>
<p>Did you know that you could edit the <b>EXIF</b> Informations of your photos by using the properties dialog of the photo?
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|General">
<html>
<p>Did you know that each photo has a context menu that could be reached by clicking on it with the right mouse button?
</html>
</tip>

<tip category="Digikam|General">
<html>
<p>Did you know that you could use the keys <b>1</b>, <b>2</b> and <b>3</b> for rotating your images?
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|General">
<html>
<p>Did you know that albums in Digikam are Folders in your Album Library? So you could easily import your Photos by simply copying them to your Album Library.
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|General">
<html>
<p>Did you know that you could customize your digikam toolbars using Settings -> Configure Toolbars...?
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|General">
<html>
<p>Did you know that Digikam registers itself as a <b>DCOP</b> Server? So you could write your own scripts automating Digikam.
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|General">
<html>
<p>Did you know that there is a Digikam hotplugging howto available at
<a href="http://digikam.free.fr/hotplug/howto.html">http://digikam.free.fr/hotplug/howto.html</a> ?
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|General">
<html>
<p>Did you know that you could reach other users and Digikam developers using the digikam-users mailinglist? Subscribe your self to the list using <a href="https://lists.sourceforge.net/lists/listinfo/digikam-users">https://lists.sourceforge.net/lists/listinfo/digikam-users</a> !
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|General">
<html>
<p>Did you know that Digikam has multiple Plugins with extra features like <b>HTML export</b>, <b>Archive to CD</b>, <b>Slideshow</b>,... and that you are welcome to write your own plugins? You can find more information about this at <a href="http://digikam.sourceforge.net/plugins.html">http://digikam.sourceforge.net/plugins.html</a>.
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|General">
<html>
<p>Did you know that you have direct access to the KDE Gamma Configuration using Tools -> Gamma Settings -> KDE Gamma Configuration ?
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|General">
<html>
<p>Did you know that you could print images using the Print Wizard? You could start him using Image -> Print Wizard.
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|Slideshow">
<html>
<p>Did you know that you could abort the slideshow using <b>ESC</b> or a simple Mouseclick?
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|Scanner">
<html>
<p>Did you know that Digikam has a scanner plugin that gives you direct access to your scanner?
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|ImageViewer">
<html>
<p>Did you know that you could use <Page Down> and <Page Up> on your Keyboard to switch between the photos in the image viewer?
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|Screenshot">
<html>
<p>Did you know that you can take a screenshoot with Digikam and save the result to an Album with some comments?
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|General">
<html>
<p>Did you know that you can use <b>PNG</b> file format instead of <b>TIFF</b> for a good compression without loosing image quality?
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|ConvertImages">
<html>
<p>Did you know that you can use the <b>LZW</b> compression for to reduce the size of the <b>TIFF</b> image files in the Convert Images plugin?
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|BatchProcessImages">
<html>
<p>Did you know that all images operations in the batch processing images plugins run without loosing the <b>EXIF</b> informations in the <b>JPEG</b> files?
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|FilterImages">
<html>
<p>Did you know that the <b>Noise Reduction</b> option in the <b>Filter Images</b> plugin can be used for improve the images rendering taken with an analog camera?
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|General">
<html>
<p>Did you know that the all options in a dialog box have a <b>What's this?</b> information available with the right mouse button?
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|General">
<html>
<p>Did you know that you could brigthen up your images using Tools -> Batch -> Color Images -> Increase Contrast?
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|SendImages">
<html>
<p>Did you know that you can use the drag and drop feature in e-mail images for to add some items to the list?
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|RecompressImages">
<html>
<p>Did you know that if you want reduce the space disk used by your images in the Albums database, you could try to use the recompressImages plugin?
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|General">
<html>
<p>Did you know that you can use the Digikam plugins with the showimg program (<a href="http://www.jalix.org/projects/showimg/">http://www.jalix.org/projects/showimg/</a>) ?
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|General">
<html>
<p>Did you know that because PNG file format use a no lossless compression algorithm, you can use the max compression level with this file format ?
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|ResizeImages">
<html>
<p>Did you know that if you want resizing images for to prepare to print on photographic paper size, you could use the resizeImages plugin?
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|BatchProcessImages">
<html>
<p>Did you know that you can use the images files from differents Albums in batch process images plugins? The process result will be merged in the selected target Album!
</html>
</tip>


<tip category="Digikam|BatchRenameImages">
<html>
<p>Did you know that you can change the timeStamp of the target images files in the batch rename images plugin?
</html>
</tip>
